>true for a brief moment in time

Outrageous absurdity and a sprinkling of pitch black humour have both been core parts of the setting ever since it was invented and have been stuck to by writers to varying degrees for literal decades with no end in sight. Hell, honest-to-God Squats came back along with abhuman cat people on a planet called fucking Carlos McConnell.

If 40k did take itself absolutely dead seriously all the time then the silly elements people complain about wouldn't be there at all given it's been a very, very long time since GW decided to dress the setting up in more serious clothes. Sometimes I think people struggle to realise the shades of irony and absurdism present in a lot of 40k stuff because it's a uniquely British thing and other people just don't get it.
